    • Method Detail

      • getReshippableOrderLines

        org.w3c.dom.Document getReshippableOrderLines(YFSEnvironment env,
                                              org.w3c.dom.Document inXML)
                                       throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,
                                              java.rmi.RemoteException
        getReshippableOrderLines returns a list of order lines which are in a state that can be reshipped. getReshippableOrderLines will requires that either the OrderHeaderKey or OrderNo, EnterpriseCode, and DocumentType be passed. In addition to the order the API will accept additional criteria to specify which lines specifically need to be reshipped. This list of liens can be identified by passing either a list of OrderLineKey's, a list of ShipmentLineKey's, a ShipmentKey, or a ContainerKey. getReshippableOrderLines will use this information to construct the list or OrderLineKey's. getReshippableOrderLines will then call the validateReship API with that list to determine which lines can be reshipped.
        LIMITATIONS This API requires an order to be identified. This means that if a shipment or container has lines from multiple orders, only one of them will be evaluated and returned. *

        Related Documents

        User Exits: None

        Parameters:
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.
        inXML - Required. Contains attributes of the address that is to be verified. For more information, see the associated input xml files.

        Returns:
        An XML document that contains the address details as well as a status representing if the verification succeeded, failed, or could not be performed. For details on the output, refer to the associated output files.
